imagine how big this is.

00:28:20.850 --> 00:28:24.105 align:middle line:84%
You could push 100
Earths through the loop.

00:28:24.105 --> 00:28:24.980 align:middle line:90%
That's how big this--

00:28:24.980 --> 00:28:25.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:28:25.860 --> 00:28:28.620 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: The power is
almost unimaginable that's

00:28:28.620 --> 00:28:31.080 align:middle line:90%
involved in the solar flares.

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:33.703 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, with the gravity
field as strong as it is,

00:28:33.703 --> 00:28:35.250 align:middle line:90%
it pulls it back.

00:28:35.250 --> 00:28:37.430 align:middle line:84%
Because if that
thing could whip out,

00:28:37.430 --> 00:28:39.750 align:middle line:90%
it'd whip all the way to Earth.

00:28:39.750 --> 00:28:44.910 align:middle line:84%
And if a solar flare would
hit Earth directly head-on,

00:28:44.910 --> 00:28:47.100 align:middle line:84%
it'd be as bad as
a gamma ray burst.

00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:48.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that
will happen one day.

00:28:48.950 --> 00:28:49.750 align:middle line:90%
One day.

00:28:49.750 --> 00:28:50.150 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Soon.

00:28:50.150 --> 00:28:50.750 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, one day.

