00:39:48.841 --> 00:39:49.715 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's true.

00:39:49.715 --> 00:39:50.930 align:middle line:90%
They're both bad, I guess.

00:39:50.930 --> 00:39:52.013 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: They're both bad.

00:39:52.013 --> 00:39:53.807 align:middle line:84%
It's just, which do
you want to get bit by,

00:39:53.807 --> 00:39:55.140 align:middle line:90%
a Gila monster or a rattlesnake?

00:39:55.140 --> 00:39:56.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, absolutely.

00:39:56.370 --> 00:39:58.666 align:middle line:84%
I mean, which one will
get you the quickest, too?

00:39:58.666 --> 00:39:59.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:39:59.520 --> 00:40:02.820 align:middle line:84%
But it's just
statistical odds are

00:40:02.820 --> 00:40:05.409 align:middle line:84%
so bad that we're going to get
hit, Jimmy the Greek wouldn't

00:40:05.409 --> 00:40:06.450 align:middle line:90%
even give you odds on it.

00:40:06.450 --> 00:40:07.783 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Smartphones won't work.

00:40:07.783 --> 00:40:09.070 align:middle line:90%
People can't get on Facebook.

00:40:09.070 --> 00:40:09.675 align:middle line:90%
They'll go crazy.

00:40:09.675 --> 00:40:10.170 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Nothing.

00:40:10.170 --> 00:40:10.600 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:40:10.600 --> 00:40:12.520 align:middle line:84%
Teenagers won't be
able to text anybody.

00:40:12.520 --> 00:40:13.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:40:13.710 --> 00:40:15.390 align:middle line:90%
It'll be like the old days.

00:40:15.390 --> 00:40:15.610 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:40:15.610 --> 00:40:16.340 align:middle line:84%
What was like before
the cellphone?

00:40:16.340 --> 00:40:18.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Maybe even
worse than the old days.

00:40:18.360 --> 00:40:19.943 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: It'll be
worse, because it'll

00:40:19.943 --> 00:40:23.370 align:middle line:90%
be like 1860, no electricity.

00:40:23.370 --> 00:40:26.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: No nothing, and
we can't survive that way.

00:40:26.220 --> 00:40:28.360 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: All your food will
be gone in the freezer.

00:40:28.360 --> 00:40:29.610 align:middle line:90%
You can't eat it.

00:40:29.610 --> 00:40:31.080 align:middle line:90%
There's no food anywhere.

00:40:31.080 --> 00:40:33.610 align:middle line:84%
You only got a three week
supply at any one time.

00:40:33.610 --> 00:40:35.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How long would
it take to get the power

00:40:35.610 --> 00:40:38.930 align:middle line:84%
grid back up after
something like this happens?

00:40:38.930 --> 00:40:40.470 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Two to 10 years.

00:40:40.470 --> 00:40:41.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ah.

00:40:41.950 --> 00:40:43.800 align:middle line:84%
Because we don't have
enough transformers.

00:40:43.800 --> 00:40:44.758 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: You have none.

00:40:44.758 --> 00:40:46.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We have
nothing, no backup.

00:40:46.290 --> 00:40:50.910 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: There's no spare
parts for the entire grid.

00:40:50.910 --> 00:40:53.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking about the
high energy generators.

00:40:53.190 --> 00:40:54.935 align:middle line:90%
They weigh 400 tons.

00:40:54.935 --> 00:40:57.480 align:middle line:84%
They're big as a
two story house.

00:40:57.480 --> 00:41:00.920 align:middle line:84%
If you knock one of them
out, there's no replacements.

00:41:00.920 --> 00:41:03.489 align:middle line:84%
It will take a year and a
half for another country

00:41:03.489 --> 00:41:05.280 align:middle line:84%
to build them, because
we don't build them.

00:41:05.280 --> 00:41:06.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: China builds them.

00:41:06.010 --> 00:41:06.810 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:41:06.810 --> 00:41:09.521 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: China and, I think,
Germany is the other one.

00:41:09.521 --> 00:41:11.520 align:middle line:84%
It will take a year and
a half to get them here.

00:41:11.520 --> 00:41:12.660 align:middle line:84%
And how are you going
to transport them?

00:41:12.660 --> 00:41:14.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they're going
to need them for themselves.

00:41:14.940 --> 00:41:15.740 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:41:15.740 --> 00:41:18.090 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: If it's a
planet hit, yeah.

00:41:18.090 --> 00:41:23.009 align:middle line:84%
If we were just isolated hit,
it would still be a decade

00:41:23.009 --> 00:41:24.300 align:middle line:90%
before we get back on our feet.

00:41:24.300 --> 00:41:26.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, if
we're isolated and hit,

00:41:26.490 --> 00:41:29.670 align:middle line:84%
how many other countries will
really come to our defense?

00:41:29.670 --> 00:41:32.350 align:middle line:84%
Wouldn't they, at that
time, say, ha ha, finally.

00:41:32.350 --> 00:41:33.150 align:middle line:90%
We got them.

00:41:33.150 --> 00:41:34.566 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, I
would the Soviets

00:41:34.566 --> 00:41:38.389 align:middle line:84%
would move in and adopt
Alaska as it's country.

00:41:38.389 --> 00:41:39.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's
nothing we could do.

00:41:39.930 --> 00:41:42.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And China
would take over Hawaii.

00:41:42.690 --> 00:41:44.880 align:middle line:84%
And nobody wants anything
to do with North America.

00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:46.130 align:middle line:90%
It's just a burned down state.

00:41:46.130 --> 00:41:48.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They'll
just let it rot.

00:41:48.690 --> 00:41:49.800 align:middle line:90%
And Canada too gets hit.

00:41:49.800 --> 00:41:50.600 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:41:50.600 --> 00:41:52.232 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, yeah,
a good lower third

00:41:52.232 --> 00:41:54.190 align:middle line:84%
of it, which is where
most their population is.

00:41:54.190 --> 00:41:56.850 align:middle line:84%
But you've got to also remember,
when you lose your power,

00:41:56.850 --> 00:41:58.020 align:middle line:90%
you lose your water pumps.

00:41:58.020 --> 00:42:00.480 align:middle line:84%
You lose the water pumps,
you lose all the cooling

00:42:00.480 --> 00:42:01.549 align:middle line:90%
for the nuclear reactors.

00:42:01.549 --> 00:42:03.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, that's
another crisis.

00:42:03.090 --> 00:42:06.730 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: There is 100
reactors in America.

00:42:06.730 --> 00:42:11.690 align:middle line:84%
So imagine 100 Fukushimas
at one time in America,

00:42:11.690 --> 00:42:13.770 align:middle line:84%
and it will all be
drifting down wind.

00:42:13.770 --> 00:42:14.700 align:middle line:90%
There are two--

00:42:14.700 --> 00:42:16.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's a
planet killer by itself.

00:42:16.660 --> 00:42:18.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, there are
250 million Americans

00:42:18.690 --> 00:42:22.620 align:middle line:84%
living within 50 miles
of a nuclear power plant.

00:42:22.620 --> 00:42:23.730 align:middle line:90%
They will all die.

00:42:23.730 --> 00:42:25.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez, David.

00:42:25.440 --> 00:42:26.700 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: It just gets worse.

00:42:26.700 --> 00:42:27.660 align:middle line:90%
Oh, don't forget.

00:42:27.660 --> 00:42:29.610 align:middle line:84%
We got another little
slight problem.

00:42:29.610 --> 00:42:34.530 align:middle line:84%
The 2.3 million convicted
killers in prisons,

00:42:34.530 --> 00:42:35.980 align:middle line:90%
they're going to get out.

00:42:35.980 --> 00:42:37.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you mean
they're going to get out?

00:42:37.570 --> 00:42:39.510 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: There's no power to
keep the door locks locked.

00:42:39.510 --> 00:42:40.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So they
just fling open?

00:42:40.990 --> 00:42:41.790 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:42:41.790 --> 00:42:42.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And they run?

00:42:42.210 --> 00:42:43.830 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: And out they come.

00:42:43.830 --> 00:42:46.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So everybody
is rioting, disrupting.

00:42:46.590 --> 00:42:47.390 align:middle line:90%
It's chaos.

00:42:47.390 --> 00:42:50.010 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And all the gangs
that's in the prisons,

00:42:50.010 --> 00:42:51.910 align:middle line:90%
they're free.

00:42:51.910 --> 00:42:54.270 align:middle line:90%
It's just the gangs will rule.

00:42:54.270 --> 00:42:56.730 align:middle line:90%
It will look like Mad Max.

00:42:56.730 --> 00:42:58.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The problem
too with this

00:42:58.830 --> 00:43:02.365 align:middle line:84%
is even if you can survive two
or three days, eventually it's

00:43:02.365 --> 00:43:03.490 align:middle line:90%
going to get you, isn't it?

00:43:03.490 --> 00:43:05.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Absolutely.

00:43:05.080 --> 00:43:05.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're
prolonging the inevitable.

00:43:05.520 --> 00:43:07.186 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: The only way
you could survive,

00:43:07.186 --> 00:43:10.840 align:middle line:84%
you'd have to have food for
at least five to 10 years.

00:43:10.840 --> 00:43:12.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's impossible.

00:43:12.160 --> 00:43:14.900 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Unless you're a big
government funded bunker.

00:43:14.900 --> 00:43:17.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You'll
run out of water.

00:43:17.470 --> 00:43:19.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Water be
the first to go.

00:43:19.110 --> 00:43:19.910 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:43:19.910 --> 00:43:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And what we can survive
three days without water?

00:43:22.200 --> 00:43:23.020 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:24.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So people
start dying that way.

00:43:24.720 --> 00:43:26.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: People start
drinking bad water.

00:43:26.820 --> 00:43:30.510 align:middle line:84%
Now here comes
typhoid and diphtheria

00:43:30.510 --> 00:43:33.780 align:middle line:84%
and the host of
third world diseases

00:43:33.780 --> 00:43:40.140 align:middle line:84%
will spread like crazy, and
couple that with the violence.

00:43:40.140 --> 00:43:44.070 align:middle line:84%
9 out of 10 Americans will
die in the first 12 months.

00:43:44.070 --> 00:43:47.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Give me the
odds on this happening

00:43:47.990 --> 00:43:51.660 align:middle line:84%
from either a CME, a
solar flare, or an EMP,

00:43:51.660 --> 00:43:54.097 align:middle line:84%
give me the odds
of that happening.

00:43:54.097 --> 00:43:55.680 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: It depends
on the time frame.

00:43:55.680 --> 00:44:00.420 align:middle line:84%
If you would say at any
time, or, you know, 100%.

00:44:00.420 --> 00:44:01.470 align:middle line:90%
It's going to happen.

00:44:01.470 --> 00:44:02.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's going to happen.

00:44:02.120 --> 00:44:02.830 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Absolutely.

00:44:02.830 --> 00:44:03.996 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We don't know when.

00:44:03.996 --> 00:44:04.890 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: No.

00:44:04.890 --> 00:44:06.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Could be tomorrow.

00:44:06.360 --> 00:44:07.750 align:middle line:90%
Could be 100 years from now.

00:44:07.750 --> 00:44:08.760 align:middle line:90%
We don't know when.

00:44:08.760 --> 00:44:10.360 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: It won't be no
100 years not for a CME.

00:44:10.360 --> 00:44:11.575 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You think
it'll be sooner?

00:44:11.575 --> 00:44:12.375 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:44:12.375 --> 00:44:14.110 align:middle line:90%
Much sooner.

00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:15.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So the
SHIELD Act, which

00:44:15.630 --> 00:44:18.452 align:middle line:84%
is what you're trying
to present and propose,

00:44:18.452 --> 00:44:20.160 align:middle line:84%
you've been working
on this for how long?

00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:22.590 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Oh, god.

00:44:22.590 --> 00:44:28.965 align:middle line:84%
Five years in my own private
capacity, last six months

00:44:28.965 --> 00:44:29.840 align:middle line:90%
on official capacity.

00:44:29.840 --> 00:44:31.506 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you
get involved in it?

00:44:31.506 --> 00:44:34.760 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: I was on my
way to Freedom Park.

00:44:34.760 --> 00:44:36.390 align:middle line:84%
Had my little tent,
and my permits,

00:44:36.390 --> 00:44:39.560 align:middle line:84%
and I was going to camp
on the White House lawn

00:44:39.560 --> 00:44:42.530 align:middle line:84%
until I could get to
see Bush about this.

00:44:42.530 --> 00:44:43.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All right.

00:44:43.330 --> 00:44:45.220 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Trump, excuse me.

00:44:45.220 --> 00:44:47.450 align:middle line:84%
But the problem
is, I was heading

00:44:47.450 --> 00:44:50.030 align:middle line:90%
out the door, phone rings.

00:44:50.030 --> 00:44:54.140 align:middle line:84%
And this guy is on the phone
named Glen Rhodes, and he said,

00:44:54.140 --> 00:44:57.830 align:middle line:84%
I understand you're on your
way to protest the SHIELD Act.

00:44:57.830 --> 00:44:58.785 align:middle line:90%
And I said, yeah.

00:44:58.785 --> 00:45:01.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Protest the fact that
it hadn't been passed yet.

00:45:01.160 --> 00:45:01.430 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Exactly.

00:45:01.430 --> 00:45:02.804 align:middle line:84%
Nobody's doing
anything about it.

00:45:02.804 --> 00:45:04.830 align:middle line:84%
He said, you're
diabetic aren't you?

00:45:04.830 --> 00:45:05.630 align:middle line:90%
I said, yeah.

00:45:05.630 --> 00:45:06.740 align:middle line:90%
You're going on a hunger strike?

00:45:06.740 --> 00:45:07.700 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:45:07.700 --> 00:45:10.700 align:middle line:84%
Doctors tell me you'll
die in about a week.

00:45:10.700 --> 00:45:12.240 align:middle line:90%
I said, probably.

00:45:12.240 --> 00:45:15.010 align:middle line:90%
I have no family or relatives.

00:45:15.010 --> 00:45:17.000 align:middle line:84%
He goes, you're
willing to die for--

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:18.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You weren't
married then were you?

00:45:18.070 --> 00:45:18.310 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: No.

00:45:18.310 --> 00:45:18.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:45:18.760 --> 00:45:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: He said, you're willing
to die for the SHIELD Act?

00:45:21.440 --> 00:45:22.280 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:45:22.280 --> 00:45:24.230 align:middle line:84%
I'm dying for the
American public.

00:45:24.230 --> 00:45:26.780 align:middle line:90%
I think you guys are worth it.

00:45:26.780 --> 00:45:28.460 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, before
you run off and do

00:45:28.460 --> 00:45:32.760 align:middle line:84%
that, this is the congressional
committee on the SHIELD Act.

00:45:32.760 --> 00:45:35.930 align:middle line:84%
We'd like to appoint you the
national spokesperson provided

00:45:35.930 --> 00:45:40.580 align:middle line:84%
that you don't go protest, and
instead, start working with us.

00:45:40.580 --> 00:45:42.775 align:middle line:90%
And that's how it started.

00:45:42.775 --> 00:45:44.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you're
frustrated though, David.

00:45:44.650 --> 00:45:45.420 align:middle line:90%
I've known you for years.

00:45:45.420 --> 00:45:45.450 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Oh, man.

00:45:45.450 --> 00:45:46.790 align:middle line:90%
That ain't even the word for it.

00:45:46.790 --> 00:45:48.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And every
time I'm with you,

00:45:48.420 --> 00:45:50.504 align:middle line:84%
we're not making any
movement with the SHIELD Act.

00:45:50.504 --> 00:45:51.303 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: No.

00:45:51.303 --> 00:45:53.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If anything,
we're going back.

00:45:53.030 --> 00:45:53.830 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:45:53.830 --> 00:45:55.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I see the
frustration in you.

00:45:55.700 --> 00:45:57.560 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: It's because I'm 64.

00:45:57.560 --> 00:46:00.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to croak
before too long anyhow.

00:46:00.350 --> 00:46:03.500 align:middle line:84%
But I sure hate to think of
all these families and stuff,

00:46:03.500 --> 00:46:04.570 align:middle line:90%
your grandkids.

00:46:04.570 --> 00:46:07.040 align:middle line:84%
Look at your grandkids
playing in front of you,

00:46:07.040 --> 00:46:08.942 align:middle line:84%
you want them to die
this kind of death?

00:46:08.942 --> 00:46:09.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of course not.

00:46:09.900 --> 00:46:11.570 align:middle line:84%
That's why I continue
to do what I do.

00:46:11.570 --> 00:46:12.370 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Exactly.

00:46:12.370 --> 00:46:14.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I've got
six grandchildren,

00:46:14.300 --> 00:46:17.120 align:middle line:84%
and you look at them
whenever you can.

00:46:17.120 --> 00:46:19.927 align:middle line:84%
And you go, I want to leave
a better planet for them.

00:46:19.927 --> 00:46:20.760 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Absolutely.

00:46:20.760 --> 00:46:22.822 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And this is fixable.

00:46:22.822 --> 00:46:23.780 align:middle line:90%
That's what's so crazy.

00:46:23.780 --> 00:46:24.738 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Totally crazy.

00:46:24.738 --> 00:46:25.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's fixable.

00:46:25.670 --> 00:46:26.470 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:46:26.470 --> 00:46:30.380 align:middle line:84%
You have, well, the
politics gets involved

00:46:30.380 --> 00:46:32.420 align:middle line:90%
and then the lobbyists.

00:46:32.420 --> 00:46:36.860 align:middle line:84%
And here's the irony, who
do the lobbyists work for?

00:46:36.860 --> 00:46:38.600 align:middle line:84%
The power company,
the very people

00:46:38.600 --> 00:46:40.282 align:middle line:84%
we're trying to
save and protect.

00:46:40.282 --> 00:46:42.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And like I said, they
should be contributing money

00:46:42.740 --> 00:46:43.760 align:middle line:90%
to get this done.

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:46.950 align:middle line:84%
Explain exactly what
the SHIELD Act is.

00:46:46.950 --> 00:46:50.260 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: The SHIELD Act
is a congressional act

00:46:50.260 --> 00:46:56.850 align:middle line:84%
that will take a $10
billion lump one time out

00:46:56.850 --> 00:46:58.670 align:middle line:90%
of the Department of Energy.

00:46:58.670 --> 00:47:02.510 align:middle line:84%
Department of Energy's budget
is $30 billion every 12 months.

00:47:02.510 --> 00:47:04.617 align:middle line:90%
That's with a B, $30 billion.

00:47:04.617 --> 00:47:06.200 align:middle line:84%
What in God's name
are they spending--

00:47:06.200 --> 00:47:06.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:47:06.960 --> 00:47:07.930 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: --you know,
every 12 months?

