00:55:31.880 --> 00:55:36.050 align:middle line:84%
stop depending on
China or Germany

00:55:36.050 --> 00:55:37.910 align:middle line:90%
to build our transformers.

00:55:37.910 --> 00:55:40.462 align:middle line:84%
We put a transformer
manufacturing plant right

00:55:40.462 --> 00:55:41.670 align:middle line:90%
in the center of the country.

00:55:41.670 --> 00:55:42.500 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Smart.

00:55:42.500 --> 00:55:44.300 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And start
distributing them out.

00:55:44.300 --> 00:55:45.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because how
big are these things,

00:55:45.670 --> 00:55:46.380 align:middle line:90%
these transformers?

00:55:46.380 --> 00:55:47.630 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Big as a
two story house.

00:55:47.630 --> 00:55:48.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's what I thought.

00:55:48.590 --> 00:55:48.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: They're gigantic.

00:55:48.980 --> 00:55:49.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:55:49.780 --> 00:55:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: A lot of
jobs, good paying jobs.

00:55:52.310 --> 00:55:53.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:55:53.420 --> 00:55:54.739 align:middle line:90%
Can you ship those?

00:55:54.739 --> 00:55:56.780 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Sure, you can
transport them on highway.

00:55:56.780 --> 00:56:00.450 align:middle line:84%
They have to have escorts,
but, yeah, they're movable.

00:56:00.450 --> 00:56:02.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We should put
them in different regions

00:56:02.450 --> 00:56:04.270 align:middle line:84%
of the country, just
store them away.

00:56:04.270 --> 00:56:07.320 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, the idea is
you don't stop building them.

00:56:07.320 --> 00:56:08.840 align:middle line:84%
You start building
them, and then

00:56:08.840 --> 00:56:11.270 align:middle line:84%
you go ahead, where
things are OK,

00:56:11.270 --> 00:56:15.650 align:middle line:84%
and physically move them to
the power plants or substations

00:56:15.650 --> 00:56:18.660 align:middle line:84%
where you need them,
and put a Faraday cage,

00:56:18.660 --> 00:56:19.710 align:middle line:90%
which is like a big net--

00:56:19.710 --> 00:56:20.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:56:20.510 --> 00:56:21.770 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: --mesh of wire it.

00:56:21.770 --> 00:56:22.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Blocks anything.

00:56:22.610 --> 00:56:23.410 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Right.

00:56:23.410 --> 00:56:24.395 align:middle line:90%
And let it sit there.

00:56:24.395 --> 00:56:27.020 align:middle line:84%
And so when something goes bad,
you don't have to transport it.

00:56:27.020 --> 00:56:29.084 align:middle line:84%
It's right there, just
pull it out, hook it up.

00:56:29.084 --> 00:56:31.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I want you to give
us your word that you're

00:56:31.250 --> 00:56:32.900 align:middle line:90%
going to continue pushing this.

00:56:32.900 --> 00:56:33.700 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: I will.

00:56:33.700 --> 00:56:35.116 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're
not going to stop.

00:56:35.116 --> 00:56:37.250 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: I've got nothing
better to do right now.

00:56:37.250 --> 00:56:39.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You think
you can get it done?

00:56:39.150 --> 00:56:40.550 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: It's not going to
be a getting around to it.

00:56:40.550 --> 00:56:42.175 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can't we
find a Congressperson

00:56:42.175 --> 00:56:45.650 align:middle line:84%
to enact the legislation and
get it on the House floor?

00:56:45.650 --> 00:56:47.780 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: It could.

00:56:47.780 --> 00:56:49.647 align:middle line:90%
No one's come forward yet.

00:56:49.647 --> 00:56:52.162 align:middle line:84%
It's just I don't know
what it's going to take--

00:56:52.162 --> 00:56:53.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Find somebody.

00:56:53.120 --> 00:56:54.620 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: --other than
an EMP hit or something.

00:56:54.620 --> 00:56:56.570 align:middle line:84%
That's the way we're
going to operate.

00:56:56.570 --> 00:56:58.190 align:middle line:90%
We're going to reactionary.

00:56:58.190 --> 00:57:00.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I had a friend
of mine in Missouri--

00:57:00.410 --> 00:57:03.070 align:middle line:84%
I go back and forth
between LA and St. Louis--

00:57:03.070 --> 00:57:05.050 align:middle line:84%
who was running for
state representative.

00:57:05.050 --> 00:57:07.460 align:middle line:90%
He was a lawyer.

00:57:07.460 --> 00:57:11.259 align:middle line:84%
John Kennedy looking
kid, a lot of potential,

00:57:11.259 --> 00:57:13.550 align:middle line:84%
probably end up being the
governor of Missouri one day,

00:57:13.550 --> 00:57:15.500 align:middle line:90%
and God knows how far he can go.

00:57:15.500 --> 00:57:19.050 align:middle line:84%
And I told him about the
power grid and about EMPs,

00:57:19.050 --> 00:57:19.850 align:middle line:90%
and about it.

00:57:19.850 --> 00:57:20.915 align:middle line:90%
And he said, what?

00:57:20.915 --> 00:57:23.880 align:middle line:84%
And I said, David, you
don't know about this?

00:57:23.880 --> 00:57:24.740 align:middle line:90%
And he said, no.

00:57:24.740 --> 00:57:25.980 align:middle line:90%
Tell me more.

00:57:25.980 --> 00:57:26.900 align:middle line:90%
And I did.

00:57:26.900 --> 00:57:32.210 align:middle line:84%
And I said, mark my word, use
this as a campaign tactic,

00:57:32.210 --> 00:57:35.930 align:middle line:84%
and you'll get elected, and
God knows how far you can go.

00:57:35.930 --> 00:57:40.730 align:middle line:84%
So he studied it, ran for
the House of Representatives

00:57:40.730 --> 00:57:43.080 align:middle line:84%
in Missouri, and
won the election.

00:57:43.080 --> 00:57:44.270 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah?

00:57:44.270 --> 00:57:45.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's a hot potato.

00:57:45.510 --> 00:57:48.290 align:middle line:10%
>>ADAIR: You know, once
the general public,

00:57:48.290 --> 00:57:52.400 align:middle line:10%
once you get them to pay
attention for a few minutes,

00:57:52.400 --> 00:57:54.140 align:middle line:10%
it don't take long
for them to get it.

00:57:54.140 --> 00:57:55.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's a
no brainer, David.

00:57:55.560 --> 00:57:56.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:57:56.360 --> 00:57:58.700 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to have
exceptional IQ to understand

00:57:58.700 --> 00:57:59.540 align:middle line:90%
this.

00:57:59.540 --> 00:58:01.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Get something
passed, would you?

00:58:01.460 --> 00:58:02.210 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: I'm working on it.

00:58:02.210 --> 00:58:04.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: All right, thanks
for being on "Beyond Belief".

00:58:04.280 --> 00:58:05.310 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Thank
you for having me.

00:58:05.310 --> 00:58:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It is probably one
of the single most important

00:58:07.880 --> 00:58:11.820 align:middle line:84%
issues I have ever come
across in my career.

00:58:11.820 --> 00:58:14.270 align:middle line:10%
We have got to protect
the power grid.

00:58:14.270 --> 00:58:17.870 align:middle line:10%
Because when it goes
down, we go down.

00:58:17.870 --> 00:58:20.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory, and thanks
